The company's policy on vacation time is as follows:
- Full-time employees start accumulating vacation from the beginning of their employment, with a rate of X days per month, up to X weeks of vacation in the first year. Taking vacation in the first X months is discouraged.
- After six months of service, full-time employees can take their accrued vacation with supervisor approval.
- In the second year and onwards, full-time employees will accrue vacation day credits at a rate of X days per month, resulting in X weeks of vacation each year.
- Employees can carry over a maximum of X days of accrued vacation from one calendar year to the next.
- Part-time employees accrue vacation time on a pro-rated basis.
- Vacation time may be taken in full-day or half-day increments.
- If a holiday falls within an employee's approved vacation period, the employee will be paid for the holiday and use one less vacation day.
- All eligible staff members receive vacation pay based on their regular earnings and are expected to notify their supervisor in advance of their planned vacation.
